{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.24",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 24,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 24 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:1",
      "text": "Wisdom shall praise her own self, and shall be honoured in God, and shall glory in the midst of her people,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:2",
      "text": "And shall open her mouth in the churches of the most High, and shall glorify herself in the sight of his power,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:3",
      "text": "And in the midst of her own people she shall be exalted, and shall be admired in the holy assembly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:4",
      "text": "And in the multitude of the elect she shall have praise, and among the blessed she shall be blessed, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:5",
      "text": "I came out of the mouth of the most High, the firstborn before all creatures:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:6",
      "text": "I made that in the heavens there should rise light that never faileth, and as a cloud I covered all the earth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:7",
      "text": "I dwelt in the highest places, and my throne is in a pillar of a cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:8",
      "text": "I alone have compassed the circuit of heaven, and have penetrated into the bottom of the deep, and have walked in the waves of the sea,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:9",
      "text": "And have stood in all the earth: and in every people,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:10",
      "text": "And in every nation I have had the chief rule:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:11",
      "text": "And by my power I have trodden under my feet the hearts of all the high and low: and in all these I sought rest, and I shall abide in the inheritance of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:12",
      "text": "Then the creator of all things commanded, and said to me: and he that made me, rested in my tabernacle,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:13",
      "text": "And he said to me: Let thy dwelling be in Jacob, and thy inheritance in Israel, and take root in my elect.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:14",
      "text": "From the beginning, and before the world, was I created, and unto the world to come I shall not cease to be, and in the holy dwelling place I have ministered before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:15",
      "text": "And so was I established in Sion, and in the holy city likewise I rested, and my power was in Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:16",
      "text": "And I took root in an honourable people, and in the portion of my God his inheritance, and my abode is in the full assembly of saints.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:17",
      "text": "I was exalted like a cedar in Libanus, and as a cypress tree on mount Sion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:18",
      "text": "I was exalted like a palm tree in Cades, and as a rose plant in Jericho:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:19",
      "text": "As a fair olive tree in the plains, and as a plane tree by the water in the streets, was I exalted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:20",
      "text": "I gave a sweet smell like cinnamon, and aromatical balm: I yielded a sweet odour like the best myrrh:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:21",
      "text": "And I perfumed my dwelling as storax, and galbanum, and onyx, and aloes, and as the frankincense not cut, and my odour is as the purest balm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:22",
      "text": "I have stretched out my branches as the turpentine tree, and my branches are of honour and grace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:23",
      "text": "As the vine I have brought forth a pleasant odour: and my flowers are the fruit of honour and riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:24",
      "text": "I am the mother of fair love, and of fear, and of knowledge, and of holy hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:25",
      "text": "In me is all grace of the way and of the truth, in me is all hope of life and of virtue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:26",
      "text": "Come over to me, all ye that desire me, and be filled with my fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:27",
      "text": "For my spirit is sweet above honey, and my inheritance above honey and the honeycomb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:28",
      "text": "My memory is unto everlasting generations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:29",
      "text": "They that eat me, shall yet hunger: and they that drink me, shall yet thirst.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:30",
      "text": "He that hearkeneth to me, shall not be confounded: and they that work by me, shall not sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:31",
      "text": "They that explain me shall have life everlasting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:32",
      "text": "All these things are the book of life, and the covenant of the most High, and the knowledge of truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:33",
      "text": "Moses commanded a law in the precepts of justices, and an inheritance to the house of Jacob, and the promises to Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:34",
      "text": "He appointed to David his servant to raise up of him a most mighty king, and sitting on the throne of glory for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:35",
      "text": "Who filleth up wisdom as the Phison, and as the Tigris in the days of the new fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:36",
      "text": "Who maketh understanding to abound as the Euphrates, who multiplieth it as the Jordan in the time of harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:37",
      "text": "Who sendeth knowledge as the light, and riseth up as Gehon in the time of the vintage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:38",
      "text": "Who first hath perfect knowledge of her, and a weaker shall not search her out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:39",
      "text": "For her thoughts are more vast than the sea, and her counsels more deep than the great ocean.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:40",
      "text": "I, wisdom, have poured out rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:41",
      "text": "I, like a brook out of a river of a mighty water; I, like a channel of a river, and like an aqueduct, came out of paradise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:42",
      "text": "I said: I will water my garden of plants, and I will water abundantly the fruits of my meadow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.43",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:43",
      "text": "And behold my brook became a great river, and my river came near to a sea:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.44",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:44",
      "text": "For I make doctrine to shine forth to all as the morning light, and I will declare it afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.45",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:45",
      "text": "I will penetrate to all the lower parts of the earth, and will behold all that sleep, and will enlighten all that hope in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.46",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:46",
      "text": "I will yet pour out doctrine as prophecy, and will leave it to them that seek wisdom, and will not cease to instruct their offspring even to the holy age.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.24.47",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:47",
      "text": "See ye that I have not laboured myself only, but for all that seek out the truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
